node.title: It’s time to start chasing your dreams..

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Julius Kähkönen in France. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text:
Today it finally happens. Me and @michellevonkalben have spent the past 1+ year more or less locked up inside but now we’re free to go. When your freedom to do things you love is taken away from you, everything starts to feel like nothing at some point and I am just very glad right now that we can do this trip. We really need it.
-
Currently we’re driving in France. We’ll be on this roadtrip for about 10 days and I couldn’t be more excited😍 Here’s a throwback to the last time I was in France☺️

node.text:
I grew up without having my own space. I come from a big family and I always shared a room with my brother. I never had any gear and actually started editing also with my big brother’s PC.
-
When I eventually wanted to grow my business further I needed my own space so my dad built me a mini office into our storage building (second slide). This served me for years and I wouldn’t be where I am now without that tiny space and cramped setup.
-
I had nothing planned for my life but I slowly built my business and started gathering whatever gear I needed to do my job. This year I got to finally make my childhood dream come true.
-
I and @michellevonkalben built this dream office together with @ergotopia.de. I’ve always wanted a sturdy adjustable desk and our oak wood desks from Ergotopia have served us amazingly so far. High recommendation if you’re thinking of investing into a good desk. This office doesn’t limit me at all anymore. I have everything I need and more. No more lag, no more weird cramped setups but a proper office to create in. A true childhood dream come true😍#ergotopia #office #officedesign #officedecor #officespace #setupinspiration #desksetup #deskgoals #deskspace #deskdecor #deskinspiration #officeinspiration

I started looking at photos I took in Indonesia back in 2018. I have 0 clue why I had never edited or even looked at this image for example🤯
-
At the time I shot images mostly to use then in my composites. I didn’t think of editing single shots back then but yesterday I found SO many potential shots on my hard drive from 2018 that are just waiting to be edited.🤷🏻‍♂️
-
Also a fun fact: this is not a drone shot. It’s taken from a hiking trail in Nusa Penida, probably the steepest route I’ve ever climbed😂

node.text: After what has felt like forever I am finally back in Finland. The weather has been incredible so far not a lot of things beat the finnish summer when it comes to photography😍 the sunsets last for hours and there’s only a few hours of darker time during the night, other than that it’s light all the time👌🏻 I slept in my car last night (2 hours ”slept”) and saw so many animals during my morning shoot. Here’s some of my favorite images I was able to capture today☺️ Also today I got my first image of a fox, swipe left to see it

node.text:
CLOUD CITY ☁️
-
For me art is often more about the process than the end result. The best feeling is when you figure out new techniques on your own and create something by accident. If I don’t find a tutorial on something within 10+ mins I always end up problem solving on my own until I find a solution. I hardly ever ditch ideas, If I start new project I want to finish them. Giving up is never an option.

node.text:
Survival💙
-
It was day 3. He got lost in the desert after being seperated from his crew because of a sandstorm. There wasn’t a lot of hope left, a huge storm was forming far away and it was almost pitch dark. When the storm got closer the wind became unbearable. The desert sand was blasting everywhere and he had to hide under his shirt.
-
All of a sudden the wind stopped. He opened his eyes and couldn’t believe what he was seeing. The storm started clearing in the shape of a heart and the moonlight revealed the most magical view he had ever seen.
-
Maybe this was a sign to keep fighting. He continued pushing through the unforgiving desert and eventually found back to his crew. 
-
No one up to this day believes his story but he’s certain of what he experienced and that night in the desert changed his life forever.

Path of Freedom🌳
-
Many had heard about the tree but no one had found it. There were hundreds of stories about this dreamy place. Some believed you’d get access to whatever you’ve ever wanted in lofe and others believed you will stop aging once you step on the island. No one knows where the place is or what power it holds, perhaps it’s not even meant to be found.
